2026-03-28T02:06:16.6192747Z             "body": "## Summary\r\n\r\n- When AWS SES rejects a batch send (e.g. one invalid or unverified address blocks the whole request), the service now catches the failure and retries by sending individual emails to each recipient\r\n- Each individually-sent email includes a styled footer note explaining it was sent individually due to a delivery failure\r\n- Fallback is skipped for single-recipient sends (no point retrying); `OperationCanceledException` propagates immediately without triggering fallback\r\n- If every individual send also fails, the original exception is re-thrown so the caller can advance `NextSendTimeUtc` as normal\r\n- Partial success (at least one address delivered) is logged and swallowed\r\n\r\n## Changes\r\n\r\n- `src/Hpoll.Email/EmailRenderer.cs` — Added `AppendFallbackNote(string html)` static method that inserts a styled footer note before the closing HTML tag\r\n- `src/Hpoll.Worker/Services/EmailSchedulerService.cs` — Added fallback logic in `SendCustomerEmailAsync`: catches batch failures, flattens To+CC+BCC addresses, sends individually with note-appended HTML\r\n- `tests/Hpoll.Core.Tests/EmailRendererTests.cs` — 4 new tests for `AppendFallbackNote` (insertion, note text, missing closing tag, no duplicate closing tag)\r\n- `tests/Hpoll.Worker.Tests/EmailSchedulerServiceTests.cs` — 7 new tests covering all fallback branches\r\n\r\n## Test Plan\r\n\r\n- [ ] All 528 tests pass locally (`dotnet test -c Release`)\r\n- [ ] Verify fallback triggers: configure a customer with 2+ recipients where one address would be rejected by SES and confirm individual emails are received\r\n- [ ] Verify fallback email contains the footer note\r\n- [ ] Verify cancellation does not trigger fallback (single-recipient or cancelled token)\r\n- [ ] Verify re-throw when all individual sends fail (logs appear; `NextSendTimeUtc` advances)\r\n",
